title: American_Top_40_1985_May_25th
description:
American Top 40 with Casey Kasem aired on radio from July 4, 1970 until August 6, 1988. This rebroadcast is one of many I have recorded from internet radio. A few are incomplete but most are not and I hope you enjoy these as much as I do.

In this broadcast:

One singer in the countdown has hit the top 10 as a solo, a duo, and a trio, a distinction shared by only Paul McCartney and Diana Ross.

Casey tells the story of the album which holds the record for most weeks on the classical album chart. It is by an artist who started his career as a man and continues today as a woman.

Casey explains how Taoism got started. Its the Tao of Casey.

Then he explains how Kevin Cronin of Reo Speedwagon couldn't go to the mountain so he got the mountain to come to him.

A band formerly known as Mudcrutch has their eighth top 40 hit.

This countdown has the first medley in three years to hit the chart.

The city with the longest name on the planet, 167 letters, has a song about it in this countdown.
